.TH man 1 "22 Dec 2023" "0.1" "simple_shell man page"

.SH NAME
hsh \- a simple shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
[\fIOPTION\fR]... [\fICOMMAND\fR]...

.SH DESCRIPTION
The ./hsh command is a simple shell that provides a basic interactive shell environment.


.SH INTERACTIVE MODE
When run without any arguments, \fBhsh\fR enters interactive mode, allowing the user to enter commands one at a time.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The ctrl+d command returns a status of 0 on success and a non-zero status on failure.

.SH EXAMPLES
To run a command in interactive mode:
.BR hsh
./hsh

To run a command in non-interactive mode:
.BR echo "/bin/ls" \| ./hsh
.BR cat test_ls_2 \| ./hsh

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR execve(2),
.BR fork(2),
.BR waitpid(2),
.BR signal(2)

